6:
Every time your smile lit up the
room, it made me want to smile
alongside you.
8:
I wanted to be more like you. Bright
and sunny. Full of cheer.
11:
But now it's too late. The sun has set.
Those days are nothing more than a
distant memory.
24:
Primula! This one here's done like a
bun in the sun! Give it a taste!
33:
Installing taste functionality this
summer was a stroke of genius! So
many wonderful flavors are now
available to me!
35:
Oh, perhaps now I will finally be able
to treat my gustatory senses to the
sublime experience they call
SASHIMI!
40:
Oh, if you want monster sashimi, I've
got some to spare! Real fresh, too.
49:
Hehe. Clear skies, a blue horizon,
and a barbeque rack filled with
mouth-watering goodies! This is the
perfect vacation!
52:
Agreed. I'm glad I listened when my
partner told me to take time off work.
56:
Is something the matter with Alk
and Shota? They're behaving
strangely.
60:
Heh. Nothing you need to worry
about. Shota struck out
spectacularly with a girl, and Alk's
bearing the brunt of it.
66:
It's summer at the beach, for crying
out loud! Can you blame a guy for
expecting a good time?!
74:
Screw Paradise Isle! Screw everyone
on this stupid island!
79:
...I could really go for some peace
and quiet right about now.
83:
Okay, let's go for a refresher, then.
How about a trip to the Miner's Front?
87:
It's a float off the coast of Paradise
Isle—supposed to be REAL quiet.
Perfect for a relaxing, serene
vacation!
90:
It's one of those "hidden gems"
people talk about! A colleague from
the Fellowship of Floof told me
about it!
93:
Nothing beats having inside info
from a local!
96:
Way back when the island was
used as a mining facility—hence the
name "Miner's Front." It's under
redevelopment now, though.
102:
Ooh... Damn, this place sure is
empty.
106:
And that's a good thing. This is
exactly what I need!
111:
This atmosphere... The transient
imperfection... Yes, this is no doubt a
manifestation of the "wabi-sabi" I've
read so much about!
114:
Oh? Visitors, huh. Came over from
Paradise Isle, I bet.
115:
We really don't have much of
anything here, but I hope you enjoy
the sights nonetheless. Always
happy to have more cuties onboard,
hehe.
118:
...Maybe this place is exactly what I
needed too!
122:
A place where a big-city guy like me
can be popular with the ladies!
126:
All right, I'm going to go for a stroll
around the island.
130:
I'm off to take a peek at the market!
Hope there's something good on
sale!
134:
What a lovely place. It's so... tranquil.
Almost like time itself is standing still.
138:
Coming here was a good call. This
place is even MORE relaxing!
141:
Yeah. The crowds on Paradise Isle
really put me on edge, to be honest.
144:
Er, not that I dislike Paradise Isle! It's
still a wonderful place—
147:
Don't you worry, I know what you
meant! Both places are great in
their own ways.
160:
That lighthouse... Looks like they let
people climb it!
163:
Ooh, we should do that too! Just
think of the VIEW from up there!
192: Oh my gosh, are you okay?!
196:
Did you hit your head? Can you see
straight? How many fingers am I
holding up?
201:
Yes... I had thought it was too late.
That it was all over.
204:
But my meeting with you...
Was just the beginning.
